HEADWORD: Xiphoid
<hw>Xiph"oid</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>xifoeidh`s</grk> sword-shaped; <grk>xi`fos</grk> a sword +
<grk>e`i^dos</grk> form, shape: cf. F. <ets>xiphoide</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Like a sword; ensiform.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Of or pertaining to the xiphoid process;
xiphoidian.</def>⟦br⟧
